  "prompt": "Is there a database with all nutritional information?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several databases and resources that provide comprehensive nutritional information for a wide variety of foods. Some of the most well-known include:\n\n1. **USDA National Nutrient Database**: Maintained by the United States Department of Agriculture, this is one of the most comprehensive databases available. It contains detailed nutritional information for thousands of foods, including raw ingredients and prepared dishes.\n\n2. **FoodData Central**: Also operated by the USDA, this is a more modern platform that integrates various food databases, including the National Nutrient Database, and provides extensive nutritional data.\n\n3. **NutritionData (Self.com)**: This website offers nutritional information for a wide range of foods and recipes, along with tools for tracking dietary intake.\n\n4. **Calorielab**: This online resource provides nutritional information for thousands of restaurant dishes and packaged foods.\n\n5. **Open Food Facts**: A free, open database of food products from around the world. Consumers can contribute information and scan barcodes for quick access to nutritional data.\n\n6. **MyFitnessPal**: While primarily a fitness app, it has a large database of foods, including user-generated entries, providing nutritional information and allowing users to track their intake.\n\n7. **Cronometer**: This is a nutrition tracking app that includes a detailed database of foods and their nutritional content, suitable for those seeking to monitor their nutrient intake closely.\n\nThese databases can vary in terms of the foods included, the level of detail provided, and whether they focus on raw ingredients or prepared meals. If you're looking for specific nutritional information, one of these resources should be helpful.",
